text.title: Brown Rabbit
text.tspan: Didn't see the point in staying.

text.title: Negligent Lop
text.tspan: Because the bar exam bears little
relation to the actual practice of law?

text.title: Negligent Lop
text.tspan: Because legal fiction bears little relation
to the actual problems the world faces?

text.title: Negligent Lop
text.tspan: Because an asteroid is about to destroy the
planet, so there's no point to anything at all?

text.title: Brown Rabbit
text.tspan: No, it's something more than that. Like, do you
ever get the impression that we're just two-
from larger currents in space and time?
Cite as: Andrew Fong, Barmageddon IV, TORT BUNNIES (July 25, 2012),
